## Hosting a WCF service in SharePoint with a SPContext

If you want to extend SharePoint, adding custom web services is one way to do it. There's several requirements usually, 
and if one of them is the necessity for a SPContext, you can use build in [SharePoint WCF Service Factories](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/office/ff521581(v=office.14).aspx).

